headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 29 points and 12 assists, Bobby Portis had 23 points and 17 rebounds in his first game since Jan. 23 and the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Charlotte Hornets 112-102 on Wednesday night in their first game <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 29 points as Bucks beat Hornets 112-102 to snap a 4-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Darius Garland hit a 31-foot 3-pointer at the buzzer to give the Cleveland Cavaliers a 118-115 win over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland's deep buzzer-beating 3-pointer gives Cavs 118-115 win over Pistons

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama broke a tie with a free throw with 2.4 seconds left and De'Aaron Fox scored 24 points in his first game for San Antonio, leading the Spurs to a 126-125 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama hits decisive free throw as Spurs hold off Hawks 126-125 in Fox's debut

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 19 points to lead the Washington Wizards to a 119-102 win over the Brooklyn Nets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 19 to help Wizards beat Nets 119-102

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 30 points Wednesday, and Bam Adebayo had 18 points and 13 rebounds as the Miami Heat defeated the Philadelphia 76ers, 108-101, on the night <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 30 as Heat defeat 76ers 108-101

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 32 points, Ja Morant had 16 of his 26 in the third quarter and the Memphis Grizzlies won their fourth straight game, routing the Toronto Raptors 138-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 32 points, Morant has 26 as Grizzlies rout Raptors 138-107 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 49 points, including 20 in the third quarter, as the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the short-handed Chicago Bulls 127-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 49 to lead Wolves over short-handed Bulls 127-108

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 31 points and Keyonte George added 26 to lead the Utah Jazz to a 131-128 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Clarkson scores 31 points to lift Jazz to 131-128 win over Warriors

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. tied a career high with 39 points on the eve of the trade deadline, Nikola Jokic added 38 and the Denver Nuggets beat the struggling New Orleans Pelicans 144-119 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter ties career high with 39 points, Jokic adds 38 as Nuggets beat struggling Pelicans 144-119

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 50 points and the NBA-leading Oklahoma City Thunder routed the Phoenix Suns 140-109 on Wednesday night to improve to 40-9.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 50 points as NBA-leading Thunder rout Suns 140-109

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 31 points, Paolo Banchero added 23 and the Orlando Magic beat Sacramento 130-111 on Wednesday night to spoil Zach LaVine's Kings debut and end a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic rout Sacramento 130-111 to spoil Zach LaVine’s Kings debut
